### Gmail Automation Platform — sample requests
### Install the "REST Client" VS Code extension, then click "Send Request" above any block.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Check Gmail auth status
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/status

### Get the Google OAuth login URL (open the result in a browser)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/google/authorization-url

### List recent emails
GET {{baseUrl}}/emails?max_results=5

### Get a single email (replace with a real message_id from the list above)
GET {{baseUrl}}/emails/REPLACE_WITH_MESSAGE_ID

### Summarize an email
POST {{baseUrl}}/emails/summarize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message_id": "REPLACE_WITH_MESSAGE_ID"
}

### Categorize an email
POST {{baseUrl}}/emails/categorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message_id": "REPLACE_WITH_MESSAGE_ID"
}

### Draft an auto-reply (does not send)
POST {{baseUrl}}/emails/auto-reply
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message_id": "REPLACE_WITH_MESSAGE_ID",
  "tone": "friendly",
  "send": false
}

### Extract tasks from an email
POST {{baseUrl}}/emails/extract-tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message_id": "REPLACE_WITH_MESSAGE_ID"
}

### Translate an email
POST {{baseUrl}}/emails/translate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message_id": "REPLACE_WITH_MESSAGE_ID",
  "target_language": "Spanish"
}

### Apply a label to an email
POST {{baseUrl}}/emails/label
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message_id": "REPLACE_WITH_MESSAGE_ID",
  "label_name": "Processed"
}

### Automation webhook (used by n8n / Zapier / Make)
POST {{baseUrl}}/automation/webhook
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message_id": "REPLACE_WITH_MESSAGE_ID",
  "actions": ["summarize", "categorize", "label"],
  "label_name": "Automated",
  "webhook_secret": "replace-with-a-random-webhook-secret"
}

### Run the full inbox-processing pipeline
POST {{baseUrl}}/automation/process-inbox
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "max_results": 5,
  "apply_labels": true,
  "auto_reply": false
}
